post_text:
Dear Parents and Community Members,
The health, safety, and well-being of our students and community are a priority of the Entiat School District.
Based on recommendations from the Chelan and Grant County Health Departments, the Entiat School District has made a decision to cancel all indoor sports, events, and meetings involving the public, held inside District facilities, starting March 11 through April 5th. Outdoor events and athletics will not be affected by this cancelation at this time. We will continue to re-evaluate the situation as information becomes available.
Should you have any questions, please call the District Office at (509) 784-1800.

Miles Caples
Superintendent
text:
Dear Parents and Community Members,
The health, safety, and well-being of our students and community are a priority of the Entiat School District.
Based on recommendations from the Chelan and Grant County Health Departments, the Entiat School District has made a decision to cancel all indoor sports, events, and meetings involving the public, held inside District facilities, starting March 11 through April 5th. Outdoor events and athletics will not be affected by this cancelation at this time. We will continue to re-evaluate the situation as information becomes available.
Should you have any questions, please call the District Office at (509) 784-1800.

Miles Caples
Superintendent

post_text:
ENTIAT SCHOOL DISTRICT 127
2650 ENTIAT WAY, ENTIAT, WA 98822
Telephone (509)784-1800 Fax (509)784-2986
www.entiatschools.org
________________________________________
________________________________________
________________________________________

Thank you for your recent support of our two ballot measures. Passing our four-year EPO levy will allow us to strategically plan for field trips, Middle School and High School athletics, Pre School as well as many other non- state funded activities for our students.

The passage of the bond proposition will allow us to replace the roof on the Middle/High School, the Elementary and the Gym. The HVAC system for the Middle/High School and Gym areas will also be replaced as well as upgrading to more efficient windows in the Middle and High School.

After the project is complete prior to school starting next fall, the building will be in very good condition for the next 20-25 years.

Thank you again for your ongoing support we are very appreciative.

Miles Caples
Superintendent Entiat Schools

post_text: Three students from Entiat that attend the Wenatchee Valley Technical Skills center competed at the SKILLS USA state competition. Drew Duncan brought home a bronze medal (3rd place) in Collision Repair. This event includes a written estimation, actual body repair and a job interview. Cam Eisenhard took 4th place in the same event. Blake Duncan competed in the Fire Science program. This event includes an objective test, a physical test and job interview. Blake placed 4th.

post_text: Our school is proud to partner with the American Heart Association and to help those with special hearts! Our Kids Heart Challenge program is kicking off on January 29th! You can get at “Jump Start” by joining our online team! Download the app by searching “Kids Heart Challenge” in the app store OR visit www.heart.org/kidsheartchallenge to get started! Start earning cool thank you gifts like the FREE glow in the dark wristband just for registering online and taking the heart challenge! You can also earn Finn with your first online donation and Ruby at $40 online!
